attachments.title: Intel managed to suck the music out of music during their CES 2016 keynote
attachments.text: Look, this isn't strictly about videogames - or even gaming hardware. But Intel's closing musical number at their CES 2016 keynote speech was such a jamboree of well-intentioned, dorky nonsense that it'd be a shame not to share it with you. There are men in red bandanas playing invisble drums. There's an entire stage of people with what look like doorbells sellotaped to their hands, lolloping their limbs to and fro to an unknown rhythm. There's a keytar.
